<br>
In this world there are many people who refuse to be told anything, or learn anything from anyone else who might know better.  In this world there are many people like Gnomos.  These are not bad people, or at least they are no worse than anyone else, they just need to get stomped on by every damn thing that's ever stomped on anyone else before they realize the consequences.  Firsthand experience is the only thing they will accept.  And often not until the 6th or 8th time.<br>
<br>
Personally I think that attitude is idiotic.  One time in a million it's genius, when someone refuses to accept what everyone else said was impossible and does it anyway, but you have to pick and choose your fights if you are really out to prove the impossible possible.  There is more than enough evidence to support the claim that the Sleeper is unkillable.  I've never even seen it firsthand (I suspect 80% of the people posting here have never seen it) and yet I believe it.  I've never been to Australia either and yet I believe it is there.  Enough evidence has convinced me.<br>
<br>
There will always be people who will do things like wake the Sleeper.  It's sad and frustrating but it's a part of human nature.  It's half of a truly noble impulse.  Now if only it was tempered with judgement and good sense, which is the other half, it would leave the damn Sleeper alone and go find some other &quot;impossibility&quot; to challenge.  Something with less hardcore evidence to prove it is impossible, and hopefully something of far greater significance than a computer game.<br>
<br>
Valquiss<br>
