<br>
It's (supposedly) the absolute highest value of hit points possible given the current system of hit points used in EQ.  If they wanted to make something invunerable while still giving it a health bar, 2.1 billion is it's hitpoints.  In order to stand any chance of killing it with anything, you would need some 1,050,000 wizards attacking it at once, assuming it doesn't all get resisted.<br>
