<br>
No it's not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> What about the Sleeper? People who don’t get SoD’s and primal are often left at a disadvantage.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
[Shawn] Sleeper’s was an experimental zone so to speak. It is an interesting concept and a great storyline. There are some social and tuning issues that have arisen from the introduction of that content though. That said, we probably won’t create another zone like it where people can’t get some items ever again afterwards. If we create content that affects the world on that scale in the future, it will be tuned more towards rewarding the community, instead of removing items and content from their reach.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> With Sleepers Tomb, once its done there really is nothing to do in that zone anymore with the rarity of the scales.  Is there any chance this could be looked at?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
When we made Velious we all kind of sat down and decided one thing we'd like to have in EverQuest, even if it's the only one, is to have one event or zone where the first people to do it would be the only people to do it.  It's a one time only thing in the game, and it's the only one in there right now.  <br>
<br>
As for the future of the Sleeper coming back, then maybe something will happen one day, but currently there is no quest in game to put the sleeper back or anything.<br>
<br>
